{
  "texts": [
    "BERT_base_ensemble consistently outperformed BioClinicalBERT_ensemble, possibly because BERT_base was pre-trained on general English corpora that aligns better with social media data, while BioClinicalBERT was pre-trained on clinical notes and the underlying semantic representations are quite different.",
    "Our evaluation results show that while LLMs demonstrated promising performance on a variety of NLP tasks in other domains and on clinical data, they are still far from reliable when applied on health-related social media data, especially Twitter data that are known to be challenging for NLP.",
    "The performance of LLMs highly depends on the nature of the health-related social media data and how researchers formulate the tasks and design the prompts.",
    "Online physician reviews are less challenging for LLMs, as they most directly express sentiments and opinions.",
    "The performance of zero-shot LLMs on the Vitals dataset is above 0.95 for GPT-3.5-Turbo and FLAN-T5, with no annotated data provided or prompting strategies used."
  ]
}